  "texts": [
    "24) and/or when the data are more representative of one class than the other [25] [26] [27].",
    "For example, generative AI systems such as text-to-image technologies Humans exhibit a small judgement bias.",
    "Fifty participants performed an emotion aggregation task (adapted from refs. 41-44).",
    "On each of trials, participants were presented briefly (500 ms) with an array of faces and were asked to report whether the mean emotion expressed by the faces in the array was more sad or more happy (Fig. 1a; level 1).",
    "The faces were sampled from a dataset of 50 morphed faces, created by linearly interpolating between sad and happy expressions (Methods)."
  ]
